    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>meat-free bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free bacon lardons are crispy, transfer the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>meat-free</strong> <strong>bacon lardons </strong>to a plate</p><p>Reduce the heat to very low and add a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>macaroni </strong>with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then give everything a good mix up</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 7-8 min or until the macaroni is tender, with a slight bite and there is a little water remaining</p><p>Tip: Don't drain the remaining water!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Combine 3/4 of the<strong> grated cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with your<strong> cornflour</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>floured cheese</strong></p><p>Set aside the <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is tender, add the <strong>floured cheese</strong> with a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and increase the heat to medium, cook for 2-3 min or until bubbling and thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>tarragon pesto </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon lardons</strong></p><p>Add a generous of pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up until well combined</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pot from the heat and top with the <strong>remaining cheese</strong> (don't stir!) and set aside with the lid on for 2-3 min or until the cheese has melted</p><p>Once melted, drizzle over the <strong>remaining tarragon pesto </strong>and top with your <strong>crispy onions </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>spring macaroni 'n' cheese with meat-free bacon & tarragon</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spring-mac-and-cheese-with-meat-free-bacon-and-tarragon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve your<strong> spring macaroni 'n' cheese with meat-free bacon & tarragon</strong></p><p>Serve your <strong>salad</strong> to the side with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
